      "writtenOn": "2020-05-28T20:45:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was specifically interested in the change in the reported runtime of this test between this CL and another one where I reverted the CL that made canvaskit accept floating point colors on all public interfaces, and that data showed me that adding the conversion to floating point colors had a negligible effect on this test.\n\nThe only thing different between the two runs I was comparing was how the color was converted and sent from JS to wasm.\n\nI\u0027m not interested in radial gradients in particular, I just needed an emscripten bound method that would take a lot of colors.",
